ROOT CAUSE: G-body(push a i0)(y) = hcomp(...) ≠ G-inner(n)(a)(y) definitionally.
In Cubical Agda, push a i0 reduces to incl a, but the body of the push branch
is evaluated with i=i0 (not re-dispatched to incl branch). The resulting hcomp
is propositionally but not definitionally equal to the incl branch result.
This prevents ua→/funExtDep from type-checking with FG-on-incl at the boundary.
The set case avoids this via isProp→PathP.

